<topic id="start-mazda-car">
    <title>How to Start a Mazda CX-5 Car</title>
    <body>
        <section>
            <title>Introduction</title>
            <p>This guide provides step-by-step instructions for starting your Mazda CX-5, ensuring a safe and smooth process. Follow the steps below carefully.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>Prerequisites</title>
            <p>Before starting your Mazda car, ensure the following:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>You have the correct key or key fob for the vehicle.</li>
                <li>The car battery is charged.</li>
                <li>The gear is in <b>Park</b> or <b>Neutral</b> (for manual transmissions).</li>
                <li>The parking brake is engaged.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>Steps to Start the Car</title>
            <steps>
                <step>
                    <cmd>1. Ensure the Mazda CX-5 key fob is inside the vehicle.</cmd>
                    <info>If your Mazda uses a push-button start, the key fob must be detected inside the car.</info>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <cmd>2. Press the brake pedal firmly.</cmd>
                    <info>For manual transmissions, press the clutch pedal as well.</info>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <cmd>3. Press and hold the engine start/stop button on your Mazda CX-5.</cmd>
                    <info>The engine should start immediately. If it does not, refer to the troubleshooting section below for the Mazda CX-5.</info>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <cmd>4. Release the parking brake if you are ready to drive.</cmd>
                    <info>Ensure your seatbelt is fastened before moving the vehicle.</info>
                </step>
            </steps>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>Troubleshooting</title>
            <p>If the car does not start, check the following:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Ensure the key fob battery is not depleted.</li>
                <li>Verify the car battery is charged.</li>
                <li>Ensure the gear is in <b>Park</b> or <b>Neutral</b>.</li>
                <li>If the issue persists, consult your Mazda ownerâ€™s manual or contact a Mazda service center.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>Safety Precautions</title>
            <p>Always follow these safety precautions when starting your Mazda car:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Do not press the accelerator while starting the car.</li>
                <li>Ensure the area around the vehicle is clear of obstacles.</li>
                <li>Never start the car in an enclosed space without proper ventilation to avoid carbon monoxide buildup.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

    </body>
</topic>
